// ========================================================
// USER
// ========================================================

// TODO As a user, I am able to log-in to the application and securely access resources (authentication and authorization).
// AC: User is able to log in to their account using a username/email and password.
// AC: User has proper role set (employee or customer).
// AC: All API endpoints are properly secured to prevent unauthorized access.
// AC: After logging in, a JWT is issued to authenticate subsequent user requests.

// TODO As a user, I am able to view all user interfaces with good UX
// AC: User interfaces should have functional and convenient UI and UX.
// AC: Design is NOT a focus of these interfaces. Good functional design is fine.
// AC: Using a CSS or UI framework is recommended to save on developer time.


// ========================================================
// CUSTOMER
// ========================================================

// TODO As a customer, I can register.
// AC: A customer can signup providing essential information including first name, last name, email, BSN number, phone number.
// AC: After signup, a customer does NOT have a bank account (this step requires an employee's approval).
// AC: Standard registration handling is in place (validation, error message for already used email addresses, etc.)
// AC: After registration, the customer can log-in but can only see a basic welcome page before employee account approval.

// TODO As a customer, I can transfer funds between my own accounts.
// AC: After logging in, the customer is able to make transfers between their own checking/savings accounts.

// TODO As a customer, I can find the IBAN for another customer based on their name.
// AC: Customers must be able to search for customers' IBANs using first and list name.

// TODO As a customer, I can transfer funds to other customers' accounts.
// AC: Customers are allowed to transfer funds from their checking account to other users checking accounts.
// AC: Transaction limits specified by employee are enforced.

// TODO As a customer, I can view account details.
// AC: Customer is able to view their own account details including account totals (both individual and combined), IBAN numbers, customer information.

// TODO As a customer, I can view my transaction history.
// AC: Customer is able to view a paginated history of transfers, deposits and withdrawals to/from each of their accounts.

// TODO As a customer, I can log-in to an ATM
// AC: Customer is able to log-in to a mock ATM.
// AC: Mock ATM provides a simple interfact to deposit and withdraw money to/from customer's account.
// AC: Customer supplies email and authenticates using password.

// TODO As a customer, I can withdraw money from the ATM
// AC: The customer's account balance is updated.
// AC: The absolute and daily transfer limits are enforced.

// TODO As a customer, I can deposit money into the ATM
// AC: The transaction is recorded.
// AC: The customer's account balance is updated.
// AC: The absolute and daily transfer limits are enforced.

// TODO As a customer, I can search and filter transactions.
// AC: Customer is able to filter transactions based on start/end date range.
// AC: Customer can filter transactions less than, greater than, equal to a specific amount.
// AC: Customer can view transactions to/from a specific IBAN.
// AC: All transaction views are paginated.


// ========================================================
// EMPLOYEE
// ========================================================

// TODO As an employee, I can view all customer accounts.
// AC: Employee can view a paginated list of all customer accounts.

// TODO As an employee, I can view a list of each individual customer's, transactions.
// AC: Employee can view a paginated history of transactions for an individual customer in a detail view.

// TODO As an employee, I can transfer funds between customers accounts.
// AC: Employee can transfer funds from one customer's checking account to another customer's checking account.
// AC: Transfer limits are enforced.

// TODO As an employee, I can view a list of customers who do not yet have accounts.

// TODO As an employee, I can approve a customer's signup and create accounts for the customer.
// AC: When approving a customer, both a checking and savings account must be added.
// AC: Account numbers must adhere it IBAN standards, i.e. NLxxINHO0xxxxxxxxx
// AC: Each account must have a unique IBAN number.

// TODO As an employee, I can close a customer account.

// TODO As an employee, I must set an absolute transfer limit on a customer's account.
// AC: During account creation and after, the employee must set and can update, the customer's absolute transfer limit.
// AC: While making transactions, the customer's account is never allowed to go below the absolute limit.

// TODO As an employee, I must set a daily transfer limit on a customer account.
// AC: During account creation and after, the employ must set and can update, the customer's daily transfer limit.
// AC: While making transactions, the customer is never allowed to transfer more than the daily limit.

// TODO As an employee, I can view a list of all transactions.
// AC: All transactions within the system are recorded and viewable by employee (ATM, employee initated transfers, customer initiated transfers).
// AC: Transaction data must include: to account, from account, transfer amount, timestamp, user initiating transfer (may be customer or employee)
// AC: Transaction results are paginated.


